==Latin==
[[Category:Latin language]]

The Latin verb, that has no morphological relation with the English " to be" nor with the semanthic sphere of the words "summa" and eng. "sum" with the others not romance attestations, develops as it follows:   

===Verb===
'''sum''', infinitive '''[[esse]]''', perfect '''[[fui]]''', participle '''[[futurus]]'''
First person singular, present indicative active of ''[[esse]]'', '''to be'''.

# I [[am]], I [[exist]]

